title: Tribune Replaces L.A. Times Publisher Austin Beutner
text:
Tribune Publishing Co. fired Los Angeles Times Publisher Austin Beutner on Tuesday, just a year after he was hired to help rebuild the paper into a regional powerhouse following the newspaper groupâ€™s spinoff from the TV business.
The company on Tuesday said it named as its new publisher Tim Ryan, 56 years old, currently the publisher of the Baltimore Sun, which is also owned by Tribune. As for Mr. Beutner, the news release said... To Read the Full Story, Subscribe or Sign In
